> We can release n-lib easily, we have experimental job (we can add more) to test neutron patches together with master n-lib.
> I understand that this is not as easy as to have everything in one project, but Networking ecosystem is still huge and n-lib is to keep common or potentially common things in it.

Please define "common things", which or what rules are used to decide a constant is "common"?
